The paper proposes a framework for early classification of time series using deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning. The paper also mentions the use of learnable decision mechanisms, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence. Additionally, the use of deep neural networks for time series classification suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper mentions optimization and compromise, which suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
